# ── Workspace lockfile policy ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
# go.work.sum is INTENTIONALLY TRACKED. The Go modules workspace mode requires
# go.work.sum for reproducible builds (matching role to go.sum in single-module
# mode) and `go build` / `go test` refuse to proceed when it is missing.
# Do NOT gitignore it; do NOT remove from tracking. Regenerated automatically
# by the go work cache on dep-resolution.

# ── Runtime data ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.db
*.db-shm
*.db-wal
velox-master.pid
*.pid

# .e2e-expected-sha256.local is the per-developer capture for the
# deterministic E2E_EXPECTED_SHA256 baseline that scripts/ci/local-verify-mirror.sh
# uses to pin the workload render. NOT a secret — derived from the
# rendered artifact — but per-developer drift would cause CI confusion, so
# excluded from version control.
.e2e-expected-sha256.local

# ── Production deployment artefacts (NEVER commit — see CHANGELOG) ──────────
# These wrap any depth to catch live operator inventories / env files that
# are generated next to test data or in sub-checkouts. Templates live under
# `*.example` (e.g. `deploy/inventory/production.ini.example`) and stay versioned.
**/production.ini
**/inventory.ini
**/inventory.yml
**/inventory.yaml
**/production.env
**/.env.production
**/vault.yml

# ── Cryptographic material (NEVER commit) ───────────────────────────────────
# Covered globally so a stray key under any subdir is excluded.
*.key
*.pem
*.p12
*.pfx
*.csr
*.srl
# Test-data fixtures are an explicit re-include.
!**/testdata/**/*.pem
!**/testdata/**/*.key

# ── Operator credential store (master + ansible-vault tooling) ───────────────
.velox-passwords.txt

# NOTE: any literal secret kept under `.velox/` on a workstation is
# gitignored below by `.velox/**`. The single tracked file in that
# directory is the operator-facing seed:
#     `.velox/production.env.example`
# which operators `cp` to `.velox/production.env` and `chmod 600` —
# the wrapper `scripts/operator/with-production-env.sh` is the only
# sanctioned reader and explicitly refuses any looser file mode.

# ── Secrets & credentials (DataServer runtime store) ─────────────────────────
DataServer/data/secrets/
DataServer/data/drive/credentials/
DataServer/data/drive/tokens/

# ── Runtime directories (DataServer) ─────────────────────────────────────────
DataServer/data/analytics/
DataServer/data/backups/
DataServer/data/dark_editor/
DataServer/data/drive/
DataServer/data/jobs/
DataServer/data/youtube/
DataServer/data/worker_downloads/
DataServer/data/ansible/playbooks/inventory.ini
DataServer/completed_videos/

# ── Build artifacts ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.tsbuildinfo
*.tsbuildinfo.*
DataServer/bin/
DataServer/server
DataServer/server.exe
DataServer/dev-hello-client
DataServer/velox-server
RemoteCodex/native/worker-agent-go/bin/
RemoteCodex/native/worker-agent-go/velox-worker-agent
RemoteCodex/native/video-engine-cpp/build*/
# ── External repos (standalone submodules — not tracked in this repo) ────
Chronon3d/
Instaedit/
Pipeline Gen/

# ── Environment & IDE ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.env
.env.*
*.env
# Operators store local env files under `.velox/`. The wrapper
# `scripts/operator/with-production-env.sh` is the only sanctioned
# reader of `.velox/production.env` and refuses any file mode looser
# than `chmod 600`. The rule below ignores any `.velox/` directory
# anywhere in the tree (root, `DataServer/.velox/`, `RemoteCodex/.velox/`,
# etc.) -- the `**/` anchor matches at any depth. The single tracked
# artifact is the operator-facing seed `.velox/production.env.example`
# at the REPO ROOT, which is re-included (negated) just below; because
# the negation is rooted (literal `.velox/...` is anchored to the
# gitignore location), a nested `.velox/production.env.example` would
# NOT be re-included and stays ignored. All other files under any
# `.velox/` remain operator-only and MUST NOT be committed.
**/.velox/**
!.velox/production.env.example
.cline/

# ── Pilot triage notes (transient -- per-checkpoint scratch from AI assistance) ──
# These `*-msg.txt` files accumulate during AI-assisted checkpoint work. They
# are throwaway operator-facing artifacts, one-per-commit, and intended to be
# untracked. `launcher.sh` (Codebuff's own pilot launcher infrastructure) MUST
# stay tracked — the `*.txt` glob excludes only the ephemeral notes, not the
# runtime scripts.
.pilot/*.txt

# ── Logs ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
logs/
*.log

# ── Python ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
venv/
.venv/

# ── Node ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
node_modules/

# ── Go build cache ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.test
*.out
*.prof

# ── OS files ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# ── Top-level compiled binary (NEVER commit) ──────────────────────────────
/server

# ── Transient build artifacts ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# A top-level `controltransport/` directory sporadically appears when a
# `protoc` regeneration attempt (paths=source_relative variant) writes its
# output at the wrong relative path before a manual `mv` corrects it. The
# canonical pb/ package lives under `shared/controltransport/`. This rule
# catches the transient top-level artifact so it never accidentally lands
# in a commit.
/controltransport/

# Accidentale recursive cp --parents artifact from local builds
/DataServer/DataServer/

# Stray grep-redirect artifact (filename created by a shell redirect that
# captured a === GREP === banner instead of piping). One-off; rule keeps
# any future recurrence from polluting git status.
/DataServer/0 (the bug vector) ===

DataServer/worker

# ── Transient git scratch notes (per-checkpoint scratch from AI assistance) ──
# These `*.git_msg_*` files accumulate during AI-assisted commit-message
# staging work — same role as the `.pilot/*.txt` block above but for git-side
# scaffolding. Throwaway operator-facing artifacts, never commit.
**/.git_msg_*

# ── Worker agent compiled binaries (NEVER commit — local build artifact) ──
# `installer.exe` is produced by gobuild inside the native worker-agent Go
# module and sits next to `velox-worker-agent` (also gitignored above). Catching
# it by exact path keeps the rule scoped; a future binary at this location
# would be discovered manually rather than silently auto-tracked.
RemoteCodex/native/worker-agent-go/installer.exe

# ── External Courser repo (standalone — developed in Courser/courserpierone/) ────
Courser/

# ── Historical local mirror (deleted 2026-07-11) ────────────────────────────
# VeloxLEgit/ was a 1.9 GB local mirror of the parent tree, removed during
# the redundant-nested-repos cleanup. Anchored to repo root per
# docs/gitignore-policy's highest-risk pattern rule, so a typo'd VeloxLEgit
# deep inside another module would NOT be silently shadowed.
/VeloxLEgit/

# ── Transient ops evidence ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Single-ticket report snapshots (rw-prod-001/003/004) were committed at
# the time for audit, then removed in the same cleanup pass. Anchored at
# `ops/` since that was and remains their canonical location.
ops/rw-prod-*.json
